post_text:
The Oswego County Traffic Safety Board has announced a car seat safety check scheduled for Saturday, Sept. 26. The event will run by appointment only from 10 a.m. to noon at Menter Ambulance, 404 Ontario St., Fulton.

Participants are required to make an appointment in advance, wear a face covering and practice social distancing during the appointment. Car seat safety checks usually run between 30-45 minutes. To schedule an appointment, call 315-343-2344 ext. 22.

APW Jr Sr High School Rebels
July 14 at 8:55 AM ¬∑

Students and Teachers- We miss you! We are creating a welcome back video and would love your submissions. Please submit a picture or a video clip (no more than 30 seconds long) with a message about your experiences with COVID-19 Quarantine. Please make sure the picture or video includes yourself and a message!

Some ideas to share are:
1. What did you miss about APW/being in school?
2. What did you gain some perspective of?
3. Tell us something that you did more of during quarantine. (family time, exercising, art/music)
4. What are some of your fears/worries
5. What is something that you now appreciate more since going through this pandemic?

APW is seeking 20 community members to take part in a stakeholder meeting where we will discuss what traits, skills and characteristics that stakeholder groups would like to see in our next Superintendent! The meeting will take place via video conference on Tuesday, April 14, 2020 at 4 p.m.

Those wishing to be on the community group will be accepted first-come, first-served by contacting District Clerk Cheryl Emory via email cemory@apw.cnyric.org or phone 315-625-5251.

More information on the search and stakeholders can be found at www.apwschools.org/Page/1321 for your convenience.

post_text:
MESSAGE REGARDING GERTRUDE HAWK FUNDRAISER

The PTSA continues to be working within state and county guidance as well as from Gertrude Hawk distribution to determine if a plan can come to fruition for fundraiser distribution within the next two weeks. As soon as a decision is made, communication will be made via the APW Districtwide Facebook page about whether distribution can happen and, if so, how that will be set up. We are working within every known detail and possibility to arrive at a plan for distribution. Due to the changeable nature of the interventions to prevent the spread of the Covid-19 virus, we may not have a decision until very close to Easter. As soon as we know, you will all know.

MEAL DISTRIBUTION

We have been approved to provide two meals (breakfast and lunch) to students who attend APW during this closure. We will be providing "grab and go bags" to all students who live in the district ages 1 to 18.

We will start delivering these bags Thursday, March 19, 2020 from 10:30am till 1:30pm. The bus will be making stops between these times and will be leaving the bag meals roadside, near mailboxes.

For questions or to opt out of these meals contact us at meals@apw.cnyric.org or call (315) 625-5241.

The lake effect band of snow is forecasted to sit on us throughout the day and turn into a region wide storm. With the safety of students and staff in mind, we will be dismissing early as follows:

JSHS students will be dismissed at 12:00
ES students will be dismissed at 1:15

Thank you and please travel safe,
Mr. Eric Knuth

post_text:
100th Day of School!!

We celebrated our 100th day of school on Tuesday. The Elementary School had some fun activities planned for the students like dressing as a 100 year-old person, doing 100 exercises, a 100th day song, and so much more!

Our favorite activity? Trying to fit 100 students in Principal Woolson's office!

post_text:
NEED A LAUGH -- GET A LOAD OF THIS!

Mrs. Stanton's classroom has been taking care of the guinea pig Buttercup, hoping to help teach the children responsibility. Principal Woolson donated another guinea pig to Mrs. Stanton's students named Thelma.

Well, to everyone's surprise, Thelma was a boy! Buttercup recently gave birth to four cute baby guinea pigs!

Each of the new babies will be adopted by teachers around the elementary school!
